
[1]wary

   WARY, a. [See Ware and Warn.] Cautious of danger; carefully watching
   and guarding against deception, artifices and dangers; scrupulous;
   timorously prudent. Old men are usually more wary than the young. It is
   incumbent on a general in war to be always wary.
